title: For Sale:  Webley Large Wedge Frame 44 Cal Revolver
postcontent: Many English large revolvers were imported by the Confederate States in the American Civil War. This gun features a "Kerr" style percussion ball tamper bar and a 2 piece construction of the barrel unit and frame unit which are held together by a "wedge" or key, like a Colt revolver/ This design is much cheaper to produce as it eliminates the machining including boring and rifling with limited access. It also causes the cylinder pin access through the under barrel lug to become redundant as the cylinder is easily removed after separating the two major units.
